<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Environmental Reports</title>
    <style>
        .container {
            width: 80%;
            margin: 20px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        h1 {
            text-align: center;
        }
        .report {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            padding: 10px;
            background-color: #243924;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        .report-title {
            margin-top: 0;
        }
        .report-meta {
            font-style: italic;
        }
        .report-content {
            margin-top: 10px;
        }

        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #031c00;
            color: #8ee28e;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 20px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        h1, h2 {
            text-align: center;
        }
        .progress {
            text-align: center;
            margin-top: 20px;
            display: grid;
            justify-content: center;
        }
        .progress-bar {
            width: 300px;
            height: 20px;
            background-color: #384336;
            border-radius: 10px;
            overflow: hidden;
            margin-bottom: 3px;
        }
        .progress-bar-inner {
            width: 59%;
            height: 100%;
            background-color: #4caf50;
            border-radius: 10px;
            transition: width 0.5s ease-in-out;
        }
        .progress-percent {
            margin-top: 5px;
        }
        .details {
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
        .details p {
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Metro Expansion Line 3B Environmental Reports</h1>
        
        <!-- Actual Reports -->
        <div class="report">
            <h2 class="report-title">Air Quality Analysis Report - June 2287</h2>
            <p class="report-meta">Report Date: June 15, 2287</p>
            <div class="report-content">
                <p>The air quality analysis report for the Metro Expansion Line 3B project was conducted to assess the current air quality conditions in the project area and potential impacts of the proposed metro expansion.</p>
                <p>The key findings of the report include:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Baseline air quality measurements were within acceptable limits.</li>
                    <li>Potential sources of air pollution identified, including vehicular emissions and construction activities.</li>
                    <li>Projected changes in air quality during the construction and operation phases of the metro line were evaluated.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="report">
            <h2 class="report-title">Water Pollution Assessment Report - May 2287</h2>
            <p class="report-meta">Report Date: May 20, 2287</p>
            <div class="report-content">
                <p>The water pollution assessment report for the Metro Expansion Line 3B project aimed to evaluate the current water quality status in the project area and potential risks of water pollution associated with the construction and operation of the metro expansion.</p>
                <p>The key findings of the report include:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Water quality parameters such as pH, turbidity, and pollutant concentrations were measured.</li>
                    <li>Potential sources of water contamination identified, including runoff from construction sites and discharge from nearby industrial facilities.</li>
                    <li>Recommendations provided for mitigating water pollution risks, such as implementing erosion control measures and wastewater treatment protocols.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="report">
            <h2 class="report-title">Biodiversity Impact Assessment Report - April 2287</h2>
            <p class="report-meta">Report Date: April 10, 2287</p>
            <div class="report-content">
                <p>The biodiversity impact assessment report for the Metro Expansion Line 3B project aimed to assess the potential impacts of the metro expansion on local biodiversity, including flora and fauna habitats.</p>
                <p>The key findings of the report include:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Description of local ecosystems and habitats, including endangered species and protected areas.</li>
                    <li>Potential effects of construction activities on wildlife habitats, such as habitat fragmentation and disturbance.</li>
                    <li>Recommendations provided for preserving biodiversity, such as implementing wildlife corridors and habitat restoration initiatives.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>
</body>
</html>
